author: COMSOL
description: The microchannel H-cell used for separation through diffusion is modeled in this example. The cell puts two different laminar streams in contact for a controlled period of time. The contact surface is well defined, and by controlling the flow rate it is possible to control the amounts of species that are transported from one stream to the other through diffusion.
